  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing shelter conditions for vulnerable IDPs and host communities in Jowhar and Balad districts, Middle Shabelle</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the context of active conflict and severe drought conditions in Middle Shabelle, AVORD is proposing this initiative with the aim of enhancing shelter conditions for 4,000 most vulnerable IDP and host community households (24,000 IDP persons) in Balad and Jowhar districts who largely reside in makeshift buuls without adequate access to NFIs and Shelter. Following need-based and transparent selection of beneficiaries, AVORD will distribute NFIs and Emergency Shelter kits while undertaking site planning activities to ensure effective mitigation of hazards and reduce congestion levels in target settlements. AVORD will employ an owner-driven approach in the construction of emergency shelters by capacitating the IDPs to undertake the construction process. In tandem with NFI and ESK distribution, AVORD will undertake infrastructure mapping exercises in accessible settlements in Balad and Jowhar to enhance programming and efficiency of humanitarian response in the area. 

Protection will be mainstreamed throughout project duration by closely coordinating with other partners operating Sexual and Gender Based Violence (SGBV) crisis centers and facilitating principled referrals. The project team will continuously identify and follow-up with SGBV survivors for psycho-social, medical, and legal support while conducting sensitization on key protection issues.

In the delivery of the proposed package, AVORD will seek Integration with other clusters hence ensuring complementarity, value for money and efficiency of the response.</narrative>
  </description>
